TERMINAL COMMANDS

Navigate folders in the file system using terminal commands using cd.


List folder contents on the file system using ls.


Create, delete, rename, copy and move folders on the file system.
mkdir [dir]
rm -r [dir]
mv [current-name] [new-name]
cp [source] [dest]
mv [opt] [source] [dest]


Create, delete, rename, copy and move files on the file system.
touch [file]
rm [file]
mv [current-name] [new-name]
cp [source] [dest]
mv [opt] [source] [dest]


Use man pages to understand how terminal commands work.
man [command]
